   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">First login with default IP address:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the webmanager slide switch is in the left position.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Connect your workstation to the webmanagers LAN port with an
Ethernet cable, directly or through a switch.</p>
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/GBMS_Connect-PC_workstation_0000527469.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">On your workstation run <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Command Prompt</uicontrol> as administrator.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Command Prompt</uicontrol> window type <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">route add 10.10.10.10 xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx</codeph>, where <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx</codeph> is the local
IP of your workstation.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Enter</uicontrol>. A success
confirmation will be shown in the <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Command
Prompt</uicontrol> window.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Open a web browser from your workstation.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Enter <codeph translate="no" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">https://10.10.10.10</codeph> in
the browser address field. A login window will open.</p>
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/GBMS_scrn-login_0000527468.png"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">In the login window enter:<sl class="- topic/sl ">
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User: </b>
                        <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">admin</ph>
                     </sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Password: </b>
                        <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">cs141-snmp</ph>
                     </sli>
                  </sl>
                  <note class="- topic/note ">After the first log in the user is prompted and required
to set a new password.</note>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The first login will run the <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System
Setup Wizard</uicontrol> that will help you setup the basic configurations
of the webmanager.<note class="- topic/note ">If the <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System Setup
Wizard</uicontrol> does not start automatically on the first login
you can launch it by clicking <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System &gt; Wizard</uicontrol>
                  </note>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </p>
